From 55909dd65aa5a7bfe03b0813bfaf4512637bfecb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 22:58:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 04/10] a/t,d/wmr: Finish the controller Kalman fusion

The merged Kalman fusion ("Broken but integrated kalman filter") was an
unfinished prototype. Complete it:

- AccelerometerMeasurement: predictMeasurement mixed frames
  (gravity_ref + q*(accel-bias)). Replace with the correct body-frame
  specific-force model, q.conjugate()*(acceleration - g_world) +
  accelBias, so the accelerometer genuinely informs the filter.

- integrate_imu_sample: feed the real accelerometer reading instead of
  the stubbed Vector3d::Zero(), kept in the body frame to match the
  measurement model.

- process_imu_data: integrate each IMU sample as it arrives so the
  filter advances continuously and dead-reckons through optical
  dropouts instead of freezing at the last pose; process_pose applies
  optical poses even when they lag the filter clock (optical latency).

- Tune the process model: stock damping (0.3/0.01) decayed velocity to
  30%/s, and process-noise 0.01 made the filter so over-confident its
  velocity estimate took seconds to converge. Use gentle damping
  (~19 s time constant) and process noise that converges velocity in
  ~0.4 s.

- Remove the vestigial SimpleIMUFusion (fed every sample, never read).

- WMR controller driver: pass NULL measurement variances so the real
  driver uses the fusion's tuned, test-validated internal defaults.

Validated by the new t_tracker_kalman_fusion test suite.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
