+		// orientation anchor. The optical latency introduces at most a
+		// (velocity * latency) offset, which the measurement variances and
+		// the residual limit absorb. Skipping the pose (the old behaviour)
+		// would discard that anchor and let the filter drift on IMU alone.
 		if (sample->timestamp_ns < filter_time_ns) {
-			printf("Skipping old pose sample, filter_time=%zu, ts=%zu.\n", filter_time_ns,
+			printf("Optical pose %lld ns behind filter_time (latency); applying. "
